(45146, 1, '2010-11-03 00:01:51', '2010-11-03 06:01:51', '[Brightcove Video]1696043719001[/Brightcove Video]Since becoming head coach of the BYU men''s basketball program in 2005, Dave Rose has guided the Cougars to an impressive array of on-the-court awards and accolades while his unassuming approach to service and the community has been recognized at the top of his profession. He was a member of national sensation "Phi Slama Jama" the University of Houston''s college basketball squad that finished as national runner-up in the 1983 NCAA Men''s Division I Basketball Tournament. Rose first came to BYU as an assistant in 1997 to help newly hired head coach Steve Cleveland rebuild the Cougar program. A native of Houston, Texas, Rose and his wife Cheryl have three children and two grandchildren.', 'Dave Rose', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'dave-rose', '', '', '2014-07-04 02:51:00', '2014-07-04 08:51:00', '', 0, 'http://localhost/ldp/htdocs/?p=45146', 0, 'post', '', 0),
