(45136, 1, '2010-10-13 00:01:32', '2010-10-13 06:01:32', '[Brightcove Video]1513254082001[/Brightcove Video]Travis is a former BYU basketball player who played professionally in Europe. He co-founded Little Heroe’s foundation with the goal of improving children’s lives around the world. Travis played collegiate basketball for two schools: Utah Valley State College and Brigham Young University, where he graduated in Health Science.  He also earned the Defensive Player of the Year and All Conference Honors in basketball while at BYU. He was drafted to the NBA, Atlanta Hawks in 2003, and then moved his career to Europe. He has played for three teams: Tau Ceramica (Victoria, Spain), Dynamo (Moscow Russia), and Real Madrid (Spain, Madrid).  Travis is also the managing partner of Yapo Ventures, a private equity group.  Travis co-founded Little Heroes Foundation with his wife in 2007. Travis'' favorite responsibilities are being a father, spending time with family and being a part of the Little Heroes Foundation.', 'Travis Hansen', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'travis-hansen', '', '', '2014-07-04 02:51:55', '2014-07-04 08:51:55', '', 0, 'http://localhost/ldp/htdocs/?p=45136', 0, 'post', '', 0),
